  "text": "Django's CharField max_length enforcement spans four key areas of the codebase:\n\n## 1. Field-Level Validation (Model Layer)\nIn `django/db/models/fields/__init__.py`, the CharField class (line 1204) implements field-level validation:\n- Line 1209: The CharField.__init__ method adds a MaxLengthValidator to the field's validators list\n- Lines 1226-1254: The _check_max_length_attribute method validates that max_length is required (unless the database supports unlimited charfields) and that it's a positive integer\n\n## 2. Form Field Validation\nIn `django/forms/fields.py`, the form CharField class (line 275) mirrors the model field validation:\n- Line 287: Adds MaxLengthValidator to the form field's validators\n- Lines 300-308: The widget_attrs method sets the HTML maxlength attribute for browser-side validation\n\n## 3. Database Backend Enforcement\nCharField max_length is enforced at the database schema level across all Django backends:\n\n- `django/db/backends/mysql/base.py` (line 116): Defines CharField as \"varchar(%(max_length)s)\" in the _data_types mapping\n- `django/db/backends/mysql/validation.py` (lines 38-77): The check_field_type method validates that unique CharField fields don't exceed 255 characters (MySQL's limitation for unique varchar fields)\n- `django/db/backends/postgresql/base.py` (lines 86-89): The _get_varchar_column function generates \"varchar(%(max_length)s)\" or \"varchar\" based on max_length\n- `django/db/backends/sqlite3/base.py` (lines 43-46): Similar _get_varchar_column function for SQLite\n- `django/db/backends/oracle/base.py` (line 131): Maps CharField to \"NVARCHAR2(%(max_length)s)\"\n\n## 4. Migration Auto-Detection and AlterField Generation\nThe migration auto-detector in `django/db/migrations/autodetector.py` detects max_length changes:\n- Lines 1252-1378: The generate_altered_fields method compares old and new field definitions\n- Lines 1334-1335: Uses deep_deconstruct (line 74) to get complete field definitions including max_length\n- Lines 1339: Compares field deconstructions to detect changes\n- Lines 1366-1373: Creates an AlterField operation when max_length or other field parameters change\n\nThe AlterField operation is defined in `django/db/migrations/operations/fields.py` (lines 204-271).\n\n## Database Schema Application\nWhen an AlterField migration is applied:\n- `django/db/backends/base/schema.py` (lines 847-926): The alter_field method compares old and new field db_parameters\n- Lines 379-404: The column_sql method generates the actual SQL column definition by using field.db_parameters() which includes the field's max_length attribute\n- `django/db/models/fields/__init__.py` (lines 840-841): The db_type_parameters method returns a DictWrapper of the field's attributes (including max_length), which is used in database-specific type formatting\n\nThe complete flow for max_length validation and enforcement: CharField definition → field validation → database schema generation (using db_type with max_length parameter) → migration detection of changes → AlterField operations in migrations → schema editor applying the changes."
}

